sentences: He continued his education in 1978 at the Creative Music Studio with Roscoe Mitchell.
One year later he performed with Mitchell, Wadada Leo Smith, and the Creative Orchestra at the Moers Festival in Germany.
During the early 1980s he toured with jazz trumpeter Maynard Ferguson.
He began an association with David Murray, becoming a member of Murray's band in the 1980s.
Snurdy McGurdy and Her Dancin' Shoes (Nessa, 1981)
Live at the Knitting Factory (Black Saint, 1987)
Duets with Tyshawn Sorey and Special Guest Hugh Ragin (Wide Hive, 2013)
We Are On The Edge (A 50th Anniversary Celebration) (Pi, 2019)With David Murray
Dark Star: The Music of the Grateful Dead (Astor Place, 1996)
